===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|bad|lang=enm}}, {{term|badde|lang=enm}} 'wicked, evil, depraved', probably a shortening of {{etyl|ang}} {{term|bæddel|lang=ang}} 'hermaphrodite' (cf. English ''[[much]]'', ''[[wench]]'' from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|mycel|myċel|lang=ang}}, {{term|wencel|wenċel|lang=ang}}), from {{term|bædan|lang=ang}} 'to defile', from {{proto|Germanic|bad-}} (cf. Old High German {{term|pad|lang=goh}} 'hermaphrodite'), from {{proto|Indo-European|bʰoidʰ}}- (cf. Welsh {{term|baedd|lang=cy}} 'wild boar', Latin {{term|foedus|lang=la}} 'foul, filthy', {{term|foedare|foedāre|lang=la}} 'to defile, pollute').

====Adjective====
